                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2358: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-07T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 7, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. This morning we effected an exchange of notes covering satisfactorily all of
                    our objections to the budgetary laws. Copies will be sent by mail. The Financial
                    Adviser and the Minister of Finance have nearly completed the preparation of a
                    detailed budget of 32,000,000 gourdes and there seems to be no further serious
                    obstacle to the complete settlement of the whole question within 2 or 3
                    days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
